      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FRANKLY (3) jumped from this box last time and also the same course and distance when a 2 length third (23.11) in a Grade 5. Safe beginner and drawn well close to the inside. Key player on best form. RITZA KRIS (1) turned in a plain run last time when seventh at Wentworth Park over 520m behind Back Tomorrow (30.42) in a NG. Has good speed and is aided by the cherry draw. Likely to be thereabouts. ARTICULATE (8) has a moderate overall strike-rate. Finished in the minors latest when third (23.37) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Expecting another good run. BOSTON STRONG (4) missed the frame latest (23.98) when sixth over 401m at this track in a Grade 5. Already a winner from this draw.",
